name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: While Congress has fought over some things, we've also worked in a bipartisan way to get the people's work done. It’s a record of results that’s making our country stronger and more prosperous, and I hope you’ll share it with your friends if they ask: “what has Congress done?”

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: CONSERVATIVE JUDGES: The Senate has confirmed President Trump’s judicial nominees at a historic pace: 84 total, including 29 circuit judges, 53 district court judges, and Brett Kavanaugh and Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: OBAMACARE RELIEF: Repealed the individual mandate tax that forced Americans to buy something many didn’t want or couldn’t afford, and ended IPAB.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: BANKING REFORM: Provided Main Street borrowers and lenders relief from burdensome Dodd-Frank red tape for the first time.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: ENERGY: Opened Arctic National Wildlife Refuge (ANWR), one of the largest untapped conventional oilfields in North America, to help keep energy affordable.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: MILITARY FUNDING: After many years of neglecting our national security, our troop readiness, and the critical maintenance of our defense infrastructure, we’ve provided record funding to @DeptofDefense, including the largest pay increase in nine years.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: TAX REFORM: Reformed America’s tax code for the first time in 31 years, putting more money in the pockets of American families and creating more opportunity for them and their children.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: PREVENTING MASS SHOOTINGS: Enacted Fix NICS and STOP School Violence Act to help protect the American people from mass shootings and fix the broken background check system.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: OPIOID LEGISLATION: Combating the nation’s worst public health crisis with a package of proposals to fight a widespread epidemic, including stopping fentanyl at the border and spurring development of new non-addictive painkillers.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: FIGHTING SEX TRAFFICKING: Enacted the Fight Online Sex Trafficking Act to combat trafficking.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: VICTIMS’ RIGHTS: Passed the Justice Served Act to provide funds to prosecute cold cases solved by DNA evidence and the SAFER Act to help reduce the rape kit backlog.

name: Rep. Kay Granger
tweet_text: VETERANS’ BENEFITS REFORM: Delivered real reform and choice to American veterans with the VA MISSION Act. Provided the largest funding increase in history for veterans care and services, and to modernize the @DeptVetAffairs’s electronic health record system.
